==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Periastron
<hw>Per`i*as"tron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>peri`</grk> about + <grk>'a`stron</grk> a star.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>That point, in the real or apparent orbit of
one star revolving around another, at which the former is nearest to the
latter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

